       " 'T1032': {'name': 'Standard Cryptographic Protocol',\n",
       "  'description': 'explicitly employ a known encryption algorithm to conceal command and control traffic rather than relying on any inherent protections provided by a communication protocol. Despite the use of a secure algorithm, these implementations be vulnerable to reverse engineering if necessary secret keys are encoded and/or generated within malware samples/configuration files.',\n",
