       " 'T1048.003': {'name': 'Exfiltration Over Unencrypted Non-C2 Protocol',\n",
       "  'description': 'steal data by exfiltrating it over an un-encrypted network protocol other than that of the existing command and control channel. The data also be sent to an alternate network location from the main command and control server. opt to obfuscate this data, without the use of encryption, within network protocols that are natively unencrypted (such as HTTP, FTP, or DNS). This include custom or publicly available encoding/compression algorithms (such as base64) as well as embedding data within protocol headers and fields.',\n",
       "  'tactics': ['exfiltration'],\n",
       "  'keywords': ['data',\n",
       "   'network',\n",
       "   'protocol',\n",
       "   'command',\n",
       "   'control',\n",
       "   'steal',\n",
       "   'exfiltrating',\n",
       "   'encrypted',\n",
       "   'existing',\n",
