       "  'spacy_doc': take advantage of trusted developer utilities to proxy execution of malicious payloads. There are many utilities used for software development related tasks that be used to execute code in various forms to assist in development, debugging, and reverse engineering. These utilities often be signed with legitimate certificates that allow them to execute on a system and proxy execution of malicious code through a trusted process that effectively bypasses application control solutions.},\n",
       " 'T1529': {'name': 'System Shutdown/Reboot',\n",
       "  'description': 'shutdown/reboot systems to interrupt access to, or aid in the destruction of, those systems. Operating systems contain commands to initiate a shutdown/reboot of a machine or network device. In some cases, these commands also be used to initiate a shutdown/reboot of a remote computer or network device via Network Device CLI (e.g. reload). Shutting down or rebooting systems disrupt access to computer resources for legitimate users while also impeding incident response/recovery. attempt to shutdown/reboot a system after impacting it in other ways, such as Disk Structure Wipe or Inhibit System Recovery, to hasten the intended effects on system availability.',\n",
       "  'tactics': ['impact'],\n",
       "  'keywords': ['shutdown',\n",
       "   'reboot',\n",
       "   'systems',\n",
